    <AbstractNarration>Abstract&lt;br/&gt;0205336&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This research pursues the development of a network of robots with cameras and&lt;br/&gt;their optimal, dynamic positioning for monitoring a cluttered scene, under different conditions of visibility. The robots must discover their neighbors, localize &lt;br/&gt;themselves with respect to their neighbors and integrate information with that&lt;br/&gt;available from the other members of the team on the fly. Further this information &lt;br/&gt;must allow a remotely located human operator to immerse herself in the&lt;br/&gt;environment. The project addresses the development of enabling algorithms and&lt;br/&gt;technology tailored to such applications as fire-fighting.</AbstractNarration>
